sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2156007
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Lux CDE With Promoter and RBS
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is a combination of the Lux's C, D, and E along with the necessary promoter and RBS's. This parts purpose is an addition to the LuxAB construct which synthesizes and replenishes the aldehyde substrate needed for bioluminescence of the product.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Carolina Sofia Gonzalez
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Addition of RBS to the structure

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K823005
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Anderson promoter J23101 without RFP in backbone vector pSB1C3 to easily fuse the promoter with other reporters e.g. the lux operon.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Korinna Kraft
